Favorite place in Ireland!! So so so beautiful 💚

I drove around (literally) the entire country in 4 days with my little brother, Toby, and it was such a joy getting to experience that with him 💚

He’s also an absolute legend!! Let me explain: I saw him a couple days before I left for Europe and told him I was going to scotland but also wanted to hop over to Ireland, to which he replied he’d always wanted to go there. I looked at him and said “bro, want to meet me in Ireland in 3 weeks and explore the country??”

A few hours later we had flights booked, rented a car a few days before the trip, met in Dublin and sent it. He also almost killed us multiple times driving on the opposite side of the road and I was legitimately afraid for my life many times 😂

But truly so much fun and such a good bonding experience. Highly recommend making spontaneous travel decisions with your siblings especially while you’re young and able to. You will never regret spending time exploring our beautiful world with the people you love the most 🥹🤍

Such a blessing getting to attend the @heartsofjoyinternational gala last week in support of this incredible organization that provides life saving heart surgeries for babies with Down Syndrome! 💛💙

It is our duty to protect the weakest members in our society and Down syndrome kids are the number one target for abortions world wide. Organizations like HOJ are working hard to reverse these stats and give these beautiful sweet humans a chance at a full, rich life. So proud of people like @laurencostabile who are actively changing our culture into a culture of life!

“What’s left of the sunset is kissing the movement of the seine. Pink and orange hues dance on the water as tourist boats pass by. Boats filled with laughing humans, dancing to music and swaying while holding each other. The sky glistens with warm pink light strewn out of the clouds as the Eiffel Tower stands strong and beautiful on the other side of the river. The night lights of the tower switch on and it feels like I’m in a movie. My book sits in my lap, my feet dangling over the edge of the stone wall where I’m sitting, fully immersed in a story both on paper and playing out in front of me. Every time I look up, soft warm light hits my face. The sound of thrashing water buckles against the wall and the passing boats. A creaky old boat sways in the water and a French flag rustles in the soft breeze. I’m alone and at peace. Filled with gratitude and joy for this moment of human perfection. Even if life becomes difficult one day, I’ll be ok because of living moments like this.”

A bit of writing from earlier so as to not forget the little moments.
